#: ../../finetuning/finetune.rst:141 152c30fcb1ef4f7ca07b688b45e27f42
msgid "**LoRA vs Full Fine-Tuning at a glance:**"
msgstr "**LoRA 与全量微调一览：**"

#: ../../finetuning/finetune.rst:143 779ebc81dc9c4905ab8e3a3ee87c07c2
msgid ""
"In internal benchmarks on single-speaker cloning, LoRA (``r=32``) achieved "
"approximately 98% of the speaker similarity of full fine-tuning, while using"
" roughly half the VRAM and producing checkpoint files that are orders of "
"magnitude smaller. LoRA is the recommended starting point for most tasks. "
"Results may vary with different datasets and goals."
msgstr ""
"在内部单说话人克隆基准上，LoRA（``r=32``）的说话人相似度约为全量微调的 98%，显存约减半，checkpoint "
"体积也小几个数量级。多数任务建议从 LoRA 起步；不同数据与目标下结果会有差异。"

#: ../../finetuning/finetune.rst:150 efbb70fd0cbe47a985702a537e9529bc
msgid "LoRA Fine-Tuning"
msgstr "LoRA 微调"

#: ../../finetuning/finetune.rst:152 9ef4485e3d75483c9f390dedc6a4d390
msgid ""
"LoRA trains a small number of additional parameters (typically < 1% of the "
"model) while keeping the base model frozen. It is the recommended starting "
"point for most fine-tuning tasks."
msgstr "LoRA 在冻结基座的前提下，仅训练少量附加参数（通常 < 模型参数的 1%）。多数微调任务建议从此入手。"

